The paper focuses on developing and evaluating deep reinforcement learning algorithms using Atari games, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of GPUs for accelerating the emulation of Atari games is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests a focus on parallel computing and high-performance computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the utilization and throughput of the GPU, which suggests a focus on computer architecture and performance evaluation, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) also likely sub-categories.
